                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 767.70/90.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-05T19:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All of the Powers save one have accepted mediation and the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs believes that if mediation be made immediately it will prevent the
                    possibility of the violence and anarchy that would result in case of a Turkish
                    defeat and the disorderly entry of troops into the city. He therefore requested
                    me to ask you to instruct our representatives at the capitals of the allied
                    Powers in the interest of humanity to urge cessation of hostilities
                    immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
